The second season of Yakusoku no Neverland. Fifteen children escape Grace Field House, a false paradise, hoping for a chance at freedom. Instead, they encounter plants and animals they have never before seen, and are chased by demons. The outside world is so beautiful, and yet is almost too cruel to face. Even so, the children refuse to give up. They are guided in their search for better lives only by a message from Minerva and a pen Norman left behind in order to fulfill their promise to return to the House to save those of their family who are still trapped within.
(Source: Aniplex of America) Note: Episode 1 streamed early on Amazon Prime on Jan 7, 2021. The regular TV broadcast started on Jan 8, 2021.
Action, Drama, Horror, Mystery, Psychological, Supernatural

The suspense horror/dark fantasy story is set in Tokyo, which is haunted by mysterious "ghouls" who are devouring humans. People are gripped by the fear of these ghouls whose identities are masked in mystery. An ordinary college student named Kaneki encounters Rize, a girl who is an avid reader like him, at the café he frequents. Little does he realize that his fate will change overnight.
(Source: Anime News Network)
Pashirare Incha ga Jitsu wa Saikyou Datta Ken

The class rep, Shizuka, was worried about her classmate Usui-kun, who was always being bullied by a trio of delinquents known as the Three Idiots. One day, Shizuka gets caught up with some delinquents in town. The Three Idiots happen to be passing by and come to her aid, but are beaten back and it looks like they are in big trouble! Just then, Usui-kun, who had gone to buy drinks for them, leisurely returns—

"Oh, your friends are still here? Don't complain if I accidentally break them!"
Thump!!!
"...You too."
"Ouch, ouch, ouch!"

Usui-kun, whom she thought was being bullied because he was quiet, instantly destroys a gang of delinquents stronger than the Three Idiots!?

(Source: MF Bunko J, translated)

Note: Includes a mini-manga drawn by Rokui Shirabe.
Konbini Goutou kara Tasuketa Jimi Tenin ga, Onaji Class no Ubude Kawaii Gal datta

"Do you want to stay at my place… for tonight?"

Kuramine Riku, a second-year high school boy, is feeling down after getting dumped by his childhood friend. He enters a convenience store and happens to save the store clerk who was being attacked. The clerk is Ayana Hoshimiya, the most popular and beautiful gal in school. The incident causes Hoshimiya to tell him about a stalker, and the two of them decides to live together so he could protect her...?

(Source: Fantasia Bunko, translated)
